    "causal_summary": "The sk-code canonical rule `code_style_guide.md` §4 \"No ephemeral-artifact pointers\" forbids code comments from embedding a spec folder/number, a packet/phase/task/checklist/requirement id (`T###`, `CHK-###`, `REQ-###`), a feature-catalog entry, an ADR id, a review-finding id, or a ticket id. The embedding-stack hardening program (and several older system-spec-kit modules) introduced ~40 such pointers across ~27 files — e.g. `// WS-1 (031/review): …`, `// Spec 126: …`, `// Per DR-004`. When a packet is renamed, renumbered, or archived, each becomes a dangling pointer that sends the next reader chasing a dead reference.",
